    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is the difference between L-glutamine and glutamine?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'L-Glutamine is the biologically active form of glutamine — the form your body uses for protein synthesis, immune function, and gut health. D-Glutamine is the mirror image isomer that has no biological activity in the human body. When a supplement label says "glutamine" without the "L-" prefix, it is almost always L-glutamine, as D-glutamine is not commercially available as a supplement ingredient. However, look for products that specifically state "L-Glutamine" on the supplement facts panel for absolute certainty. All products in our evaluation use L-Glutamine.' },
    },
  ],
};
